  ● Discard binds an expression with no value
   ╭─[test.lis:6:3]
 5 │   let mut o = Options{ port: "" }
 6 │   let _ = configure(&o)
   ·   ──────────┬──────────
   ·             ╰── this expression produces no value to discard
 7 │   let _ = o.port
   ╰────
  help: Remove `let _ = ` and keep the expression as a statement. A `let _ = ` discard is only meaningful when the expression produces a value · code: [lint.discarded_unit_binding]
